The Investors and Exporters (I&E) FX window opened at N364.66, traded high at N365.50 and eventually closed at N364.00, representing a 0.14 per cent  appreciation against last Friday’s closing price. A total of $211.48 million was transacted through the I&E window on the last day of trading in 2018. At the parallel market, the cash rate depreciated slightly by 0.14 per cent to N360.00/$, while the transfer rate appreciated firmly by 0.55 per cent to N364.00/$. The Naira at the inter-bank rate remained unchanged to closed at N307.00 against last Friday’s closing price. © 2018, Hallmarknews. All rights reserved. Reference and link to this site is required if you wish to reuse any article. comments and opinions